<paragraph id="E97036DD3F06FF91FF76FAC9FC24FA88" blockId="51.[151,1437,1358,1925]" box="[151,964,1358,1385]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Size. Maximum size about 
<quantity id="2E379B383F06FF91FE28FAC8FDF5FA88" box="[457,533,1358,1385]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" unit="cm" value="5.4">5.4 cm</quantity>
total length (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F06FF91FD48FAC9FC58FA88" author="Kovtun, O. A. &amp; Manilo, L. G." box="[681,952,1359,1385]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="307 - 314" refId="ref59524" refString="Kovtun, O. A. &amp; Manilo, L. G. (2013) Mediterranean fish - Gammogobius steinitzi Bath, 1971 (Actinopterygii: Perciformes: Gobiidae) - a new representative of the Black Sea ichthyofauna. Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 43, 307 - 314. https: // doi. org / 10.3750 / AIP 2013.43.4.08" type="journal article" year="2013">
Kovtun &amp; 
<collectingRegion id="2B0BF83F3F06FF91FCC2FAC9FC94FA88" box="[803,884,1359,1385]" country="Philippines" name="Manila" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Manilo</collectingRegion>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1D565563F06FF91FF26FAF5FA77F864" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="description">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F06FF91FF26FAF5FC53F9FC" blockId="51.[151,1437,1358,1925]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Morphology. D VI + I,8–9; A I,7–9; P 15–17 (summarized in 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F06FF91FC97FAF5FB62FA6C" author="Kovtun, O. A. &amp; Manilo, L. G." box="[886,1154,1395,1421]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="307 - 314" refId="ref59524" refString="Kovtun, O. A. &amp; Manilo, L. G. (2013) Mediterranean fish - Gammogobius steinitzi Bath, 1971 (Actinopterygii: Perciformes: Gobiidae) - a new representative of the Black Sea ichthyofauna. Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 43, 307 - 314. https: // doi. org / 10.3750 / AIP 2013.43.4.08" type="journal article" year="2013">
Kovtun &amp; 
<collectingRegion id="2B0BF83F3F06FF91FC0CFAF5FBDEFA6C" box="[1005,1086,1395,1421]" country="Philippines" name="Manila" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Manilo</collectingRegion>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). Small goby with stocky body, 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F06FF91FF3CFA11FCC4FA50" bold="true" box="[221,804,1430,1457]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">large depressed head and a gently sloping snout</emphasis>
. Eyes large, with a narrow interorbital space (
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F06FF91FAD8FA11FA70FA50" box="[1337,1424,1431,1457]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="24.[151,250,2000,2024]" captionTargetBox="[173,1414,1146,1976]" captionTargetId="figure-43@24.[173,1414,1146,1976]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 22. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gammogobius steinitzi Bath, 1971. Photo by S. Guerrieri, Tuscany, Italy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601635/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Caudal peduncle deep, almost as deep as the body. Dorsal fins of similar height, the first dorsal fin with more or less rounded shape and no elongated spines, all but the sixth spines being subequal in length. Caudal fin rounded. Scales visible on body from reticulate pigmentation pattern along scale edges.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F06FF91FF26F9A1FD29F94C" blockId="51.[151,1437,1358,1925]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Live coloration. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F06FF91FE68F9A1FEC7F984" bold="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Body with barred coloration pattern of 6–7 narrow pale bars on a mostly brownish background</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F06FF91FED6F9CDFE6BF984" box="[311,395,1611,1637]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="24.[151,250,2000,2024]" captionTargetBox="[173,1414,1146,1976]" captionTargetId="figure-43@24.[173,1414,1146,1976]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 22. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gammogobius steinitzi Bath, 1971. Photo by S. Guerrieri, Tuscany, Italy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601635/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Head brownish with 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F06FF91FD66F9CCFE16F969" bold="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">3 pale, continuous bars extending downwards from eye over cheek and preopercle to ventral side</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F06FF91FDE5F9E9FD86F96B" box="[516,614,1647,1674]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,1212,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-41@23.[154,1434,1212,1864]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 20. Three pale, uninterrupted bars (marked with numbers) extending downwards from eye radiating downwards from eye to ventral side: A) C. liechtensteini, B) G. steinitzi. Photos by M. Kovačić (fishes photographed in a tank)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601629" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601629/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 20b</figureCitation>
). Fins mostly colorless; some 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F06FF91FC53F9E9FDADF94D" bold="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">black spots at the base of both dorsal fins, extending as dots along rays or spine</emphasis>
s (
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F06FF91FD89F915FD5CF94C" box="[616,700,1683,1709]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="24.[151,250,2000,2024]" captionTargetBox="[173,1414,1146,1976]" captionTargetId="figure-43@24.[173,1414,1146,1976]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 22. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gammogobius steinitzi Bath, 1971. Photo by S. Guerrieri, Tuscany, Italy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601635/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F06FF91FF26F931FC33F930" blockId="51.[151,1437,1358,1925]" box="[199,979,1719,1745]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Similar species. 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F06FF91FE9EF931FD21F930" authorityName="Benthic" baseAuthorityName="Kolombatovic" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[383,705,1719,1745]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Corcyrogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="liechtensteini">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F06FF91FE9EF931FD21F930" box="[383,705,1719,1745]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Corcyrogobius liechtensteini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F06FF91FD31F931FC2CF930" authorityName="Ahnelt &amp; Patzner" authorityYear="1995" box="[720,972,1719,1745]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Didogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="splechtnai">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F06FF91FD31F931FC2CF930" box="[720,972,1719,1745]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Didogobius splechtnai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F06FF91FF26F95DFB9CF8F8" blockId="51.[151,1437,1358,1925]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Habitat. Infralittoral species, known from 
<quantity id="2E379B383F06FF91FD51F95CFCE8F914" box="[688,776,1754,1781]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" unit="m" value="15.0" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="5.0">5–25 m</quantity>
in marine caves, more common in deeper water. Mostly inhabits the crevices and holes of cave walls and ceilings (summarized by 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F06FF91FC38F979FB90F8F8" author="Patzner, R. A." box="[985,1136,1791,1817]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refId="ref62855" refString="Patzner, R. A. (2021) Gobiidae. Available from: http: // www. patzner. sbg. ac. at / Gobiidae / GobiidaeSpecies. htm (accessed 1 October 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Patzner 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
